Hypnotic cheese!!! El Miner is a cheese made with raw unpasteurised goats milk: intense flavours of umami, quite salty and earthy aromas...I‚Äôd say do it this or that way, but it would be useless: eat it as you want, it‚Äôs unbelievable! The 6 months of ageing done in the small villages of Espinelves, in the inland of rural Catalunya, has done miracles to achieve THE perfect taste in a cheese üßÄüòãüò¨ #cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #cheese #goatcheese #perfection #cook #taste #inspire

I love food, but also art, so that‚Äôs the idea behind making this ‚ÄúSelf Portrait with fredolic‚Äù like Piero della Francesca would have done itüòÇüòÇüòÇ ‚ÄúFredolics‚Äù are some really strange mushrooms, quite intense in flavour, a firm texture, a slight scent of wood makes them ideal to cook in meat stews! However, as it‚Äôs one of my principles: when the product is good there‚Äôs no need to do many things to it, pan fried are a glorious biteüòãüò¨ To find them look in pine woods from late August to late November and do not ask me a precise spot because even if I knew it I would never ever tellüòÇüòú #cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #mushrooms #farmtotable #forage #fredolics #costabrava #cook #taste #inspire

I know I look like a psycho, but there‚Äôs a reason to get so many peppers: cooking ‚Äúsamfaina‚Äù, an utterly typical dish from Catalunya! It should be done with eggplants, onions, zucchini and a little bit of tomato, however you can change the recipe and add or take some different veggies... Just need to pan fry everything until it‚Äôs fairly soft and then it‚Äôs good to go on its own and some bread, to cook something in it (pork meat goes really well) or to use to add to a dish as a side! Next time you see some mad person buying too many peppers just check if it‚Äôs me üòÇüòú #cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #samfaina #peppers #palamos #cook #taste #inspire

Sooo many different and delicious peppers...üòã Of all the bunch in here I really enjoyed the small red bell peppers which were perfect in every sense and the ‚ÄúPadr√≤n‚Äù peppers: similar to shishito peppers (from Japan) are a little bit more chubby and with some lovely, and unexpected, purple patches! Cooking them it‚Äôs easy, just pan fry them with olive oil and then add some Maldon salt, however it‚Äôs a little bit of a gamble as some of them could be spicy... those ones were the closest thing to be eating napalmüòÇüòÇüòÇ
#cookingclass #homecooking #farmtotable #peppers #market #palamos #cook #taste #inspire

Peppers, peppers, peppers!!!üò¨ Here they grow almost all year round, however with more sun more flavour... Bellania violet peppers are super sweet, great for any kind of salad or eaten raw, delicate scent and with a really interesting dark colour (beware they loose it when cooked)! Now I‚Äôm just trying to see where I could get some seeds and start growing them, it‚Äôs definitely the most fashionable of all peppersüòÇüòÇüòÇ
#cookingclass #homecooking #farmtotable #fresh #market #palamos #costabrava #cook #taste #inspire

A normal day in the kitchenüòú A little bit of everything, but what I really love it‚Äôs the gorgeous seafood you can easily get at almost any market in Barcelona (in this case everything comes from the Mercat de l‚ÄôAbaceria Central in Gr√†cia): -Mantis shrimp on the top right which I use to make fish stock, the season it‚Äôs just started and they are cheap and soooo tasty üòã -In the middle a live langoustine that was marinated in orange juice, extra virgin olive oil and maldon salt and eaten rawü§§ -In the white bowl some Bouchot mussels, as now it‚Äôs not the right season for the ones from Delta this species farmed in France is of great quality and always a good option if, like myself, you don‚Äôt really like the massive ones coming from Galicia üò¨ -Palam√≥s prawns in the bottom (red prawns) that are just sublime in every single way, they are so good they should be forbidden üòÖ -And lost in the photo also some clams from Galicia, in my opinion much much much better then oysters when eaten raw ü§©

#cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #market #farmtotable #seafood #cook #taste #inspire

There seems to be a quite severe scarcity of mushrooms this year, however I‚Äôve managed to try these really rare, expensive and at the same time delicious mushrooms: ‚Äúous de reig‚Äù (king eggs; also known in Italy as ‚Äúovuli‚Äù)! It‚Äôs the most similar thing to porcini: great texture and a strong but balanced flavour. I wish I could tell you where to get those, but in all my life I‚Äôve never seen one in the wild...that‚Äôs probably why they can easily get to 100+ ‚Ç¨ per kiloüò≥üòãü§§

Catch of the day!!! These are rock crabs that can be found everywhere on the Mediterranean coast, they live in small hollows or cracks in the rocks and are freaking difficult to get outüòÇüòÇüòÇ On the good side they are not sold anywhere, so catching them it‚Äôs the only way you have to try their sweet and flavourful meat, just perfect for a great pasta sauce üòéüòúü§§ #cookingclass #homecooking #costabrava #catchoftheday #crab #cook #taste #inspire

And here some ‚Äúmongetes del ganxet‚Äù (white beans) which I bought fresh: usually we tend to buy dried legumes, and it‚Äôs a little tricky as it takes quite a lot of time to have them ready...soaking them in water for 24hrs and then cooking them at low temperature for quite a while...üòë But with the fresh ones it‚Äôs so much easier, just need to thresh them, then put in a pot with very little water, salt, a bay leaf and a few drops of wine vinegar! When ready just stir fry them lightly adding some freshly chopped parsley at the end and you‚Äôll be in heaven üòã‚ò∫Ô∏èüòú

Tomatoes from ‚ÄúBarbastro‚Äù (Huesca, Spain) are one of my weaknesses, and the season for them is coming to an end! They are normally used for salads as are meaty and with a great flavour, however I like to get really mature ones and use them to make gazpacho üçÖüçÖüçÖ Also when  getting those the price is in average half of what you would pay for a normal ripened one and believe me they can get pretty expensive üòÇüí∏

This is my present dream...chanterelles are so tasty it‚Äôs almost impossible to verbalise how good they are! Just waiting for it to rain a bit and off we go, mushroom picking üòå Last time I went it was full everywhere...of poisonous onesüòÇüòÇüòÇ

My beloved capers: a plant that can grow directly on walls and of which you can actually use everything! Yes, unlike most people think you can eat the caper (which is a flower), the fruit (‚Äúalcaparr√≥n‚Äù in Spanish) and also the leafs: in Santorini they preserve them with salt and olive oil and are great in salads and seafood dishes! Next step will be trying to grow my own üòäüòÅ‚ò∫Ô∏è #cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #capers #foraging #cook #taste #inspire

Here at Acetaia Leonardi (@leonardi_lifestyle) between what I consider liquid gold: balsamic vinegar from Modena! Here they grow grapes of the variety Lambrusco and Trebbiano in the estate to produce their balsamic vinegar in different types of barrels, cherry tree and oak wood are just a couple of examples. The vinegar is racked from bigger to smaller barrels until it gets a certain thickness! How cool is that? Not to mention myself üòÇüòÇüòÇ #cookingclass #homecooking #balsamicvinegar #acetaialeonardi #modena #italy #cook #taste #inspire

And this what I did in my last trip to Italy...we went to the Apennino Tosco-Emiliano, but I will never tell the exact location üòÇüòÇüòÇ We were struggling at the beginning but by the end of the morning we found a couple of kilos of wonderful porcini (Boletus edulis). It‚Äôs incredible how difficult is to spot them, but the reward is amazing! I did a few (just the caps) raw, cutting them really thin and then dressing with olive oil, pepper and salt; the rest I was used to make a white sauce for tagliatelle ü§§ü§§ü§§

These are green walnuts, the main ingredient for the ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù! The tradition tells you to pick them up on the day of Saint John (end of June, the summer solstice) however if they are still green there‚Äôs no need to be so precise... ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù is not only a Catalan spirit as it exists in different countries with slightly different recipes: in Italy we would call it ‚ÄúNocino‚Äù and it‚Äôs a bit sweeter than the one from Catalunya, but still pretty good!!!üòäüòúüòã
#cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #walnuts #ratafia #cook #taste #inspire

Lavender is such a gorgeous plant: doesn‚Äôt need much water to grow, looks great and smells even better! The extrac from the plant is used commonly in sweets and pastries, however it‚Äôs also an interesting ingredient when used to produce spirits: I added just a bit in the mix for my ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù and I hope that the sweet scent will make it a little bit more complex... As many other things like rosemary or thyme it‚Äôs quite powerful so if you ever use it be careful of not adding too much üòäüòÅüòú

The Mediterranean area is known to be the place for aromatic herbs, you could stumble on one without even looking for it! This is thyme from the hills of Osona, its scent can be noticed from quite far away as they tend to grow in big colonies so, if you find one plant usually there‚Äôll be plenty around! This is another of the ingredients I used for my ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù just to give a kick to its flavour, however be careful as too much could ruin everything üòúüòÅüòä
#cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #thyme #mediterraneo #ratafia #cook #taste #inspire

Another thing you can get in the biggest supermarket on earth: nature! Every time I see blackberries sold I can‚Äôt believe how people can spend so much money on a tiny box when it‚Äôs actually something that you can forage everywhere from mid-August to mid-September! Blackberries are now at its best, sweet, fat and juicy: the ones on the photo have been used to make ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù, I hope that the sweetness and dark colour can pass on to the spirit in order for it to be more complex and tasty üòãüòäüòÅ
#cookingclass #homecooking #barcelona #foraging #blackberries #ratafia #cook #taste #inspire

Wild fennel flowers are quite a thing at this time of the year: the plant loses almost all the thin leafs and all it remains are the flowers! You can do as many things as with the leafs and stalks, they are still edible, the flavour is like anise but a bit sweeter than the other parts of the plant... I‚Äôve used them to do my first ever ‚ÄúRatafia‚Äù, hope they do some magicüòäüòÅüòú
